==English==
{{wikipedia|tilting at windmills}}

===Alternative forms===
* {{l|en|fight windmills}}

===Etymology===
From a passage in the novel [[w:Don Quixote|Don Quixote]] where the eponymous character tilts (i.e. [[joust]]s) at [[windmill]]s that he has mistaken for giants.

===Verb===
{{head|en|verb}}

# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To [[attack]] [[imaginary]] [[enemies]].
# {{lb|en|intransitive|by extension}} To go on a [[wild-goose chase]]; to [[persistently]] engage in a [[futile]] [[activity]].

